## Description {#details}

Extended <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/value">Value</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/type">Type</a>.

Capable of holding value types which are not native for any processor (such as the i12345 type), as well as the types an <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mvt">MVT</a> can represent.

Definition at line 35 of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/codegen/valuetypes-h">ValueTypes.h</a>.

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>EVT EVT::getEVT (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/type">Type</a> &#42; Ty, bool HandleUnknown=false)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
Return the value type corresponding to the specified type.

getEVT - Return the value type corresponding to the specified type.

If HandleUnknown is true, unknown types are returned as Other, otherwise they are invalid. NB: This includes pointer types, which require a <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/datalayout">DataLayout</a> to convert to a concrete value type.
